Minister of Trade and Industry Rob Davies announced on Tuesday that Busi Mabuza would head up the new Brics Business Council. Mabuza is the chair of the Industrial Development Corporation.   The five new members of the council are The council, established in 2012, aims to promote and strengthen business, trade and investment ties between the five Brics countries. The previous chair of the SA council was Iqbal Survé of Sekunjalo. 